in
the third quarter of 2008, the company made discretionary contributions
totaling $200 million to its u.s. qualified pension plan. in 2009, the company
expects to contribute an amount in the range of $600 million to $850 million to
its u.s. and international pension plans. the company does not have a required
minimum pension contribution obligation for its u.s. plans in 2009. therefore,
the amount of the anticipated discretionary contribution could vary
significantly depending on the u.s. plans funding status as of the 2009
measurement date and the anticipated tax deductibility of the contribution.
