18. geographic areas
geographic area
information is used by the company as a secondary performance measure to manage
its businesses. effective in the first quarter of 2008, the company changed its
allocations of research, development and related expenses (r&d) to more
closely align these costs with the geographic areas that benefit. thus,
operating income information presented below has been updated for all periods
presented to reflect these changes, with no change in worldwide results. export
sales and certain income and expense items are generally reported within the
geographic area where the final sales to 3m customers are made.
